    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 (D) E.D.B./1974: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-05T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 5, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1325. Your 1849, October 30, 1942, 11 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d87fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> To countries listed in Department’s 1296, October 28, 8 p.m.
                    please add 5.84 percent for Uruguay. Department feels that exports from Chile to
                    other American republics in excess of the percentage indicated should be
                    permitted when conditions warrant and when approved by both Chilean and United
                    States Governments.</p>
                <pb facs="0089" n="75" xml:id="pg_75"/>
                <p>The Department feels that the percentage basis is the fairest approach for making
                    allocations in order that all the republics may be treated in a similar
                    manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
